				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$_{\text {ari+aci}} > -~1.6\text {~W~m}^{-2}$\end{document}, which is not a meaningful narrowing of the consensus range. This point is also illustrated by the experience that models with a historical aerosol forcing sufficiently strong to produce a counterfactual cooling during the second half of the 20th century lie far outside the accepted range of ERFaci [46], again providing no more stringent a constraint than ERFari+aci>−1.6W m−2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
